Heyla,
  according to the manual:
``A "/" at the end of a pattern is equivalent to "(/)".''

% setopt markdirs
% mkdir foo
% ln -s foo bar
% echo */
bar foo/
% echo *(/)
foo/

It even recognises that bar is not a directory.
